claim.claim-text:
1. A process for automatically calibrating gas sensors comprising: 
connecting a calibrating gas tube to teach sensor; 
introducing span gas into the sensor calibration tube manifold; 
waiting a predetermined time for the span gas to travel to each sensor and for the sensors to register the span gas in a stable fashion; 
detecting the raw digital value being transmitted for each sensor and assigning the calibrated values to the proper sensor configuration registers; 
terminating the span gas flow; 
introducing zero gas into the sensor calibrating tube manifold; 
waiting a predetermined time for the zero gas to travel to each sensor and for the sensors to register the zero gas in a stable fashion; 
assigning calibrated zero values to the sensor registers; 
turning of the zero gas flow.

10. Apparatus for automatically calibrating gas sensors comprising: 
a calibration gas tube connected to each sensor; 
a source of span gas and a source of zero gas; 
means to control introduction and termination of span gas and zero gas to each sensor.
